jmf.data

Class MessageType

  • java.lang.Object
    • jmf.data.MessageType

  • public class MessageType
extends java.lang.Object
    Data structure discribing the type of a message. Consists of a string of match up to 32 bytes describing the message. Is used for message filtering in ZMQ. Can be bulded with the MessageTypeBuilder. created on 7/25/15.
    Author:
    Tobias Korb, Jan Strau√ü, Andre Kutzleb

      • overridePrefixWith

        public void overridePrefixWith(MessageType other)
        Changes the prefix of this messageType with the given MessageType. For Example if this MessageType contains "AABBCC" and the given MessageType consists of "QQE", this MessageType will end up containing "QQEBCC".
        Parameters:
        other - the new prefix
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given MessageType is longer than this MessageType

      • containsTopic

        public boolean containsTopic(MessageType other)
        Checks if this message type contains the other message type. A Contains B if and only if: A.length smaller equals B.length and all indices in A and B for the full range of A are the same
        Parameters:
        other - the other message type to check if it is contained in this messageType.
        Returns:
        true if this message type "contains" the given message type, false otherwise
